      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are right to point out that when strict rules regarding language become tools for social control, the ultimate goal shifts from fostering progress to enforcing conformity. While the original intention of social justice movements is progress, rigid enforcement can indeed stifle genuine discourse by punishing individuals for unintentional mistakes rather than addressing systemic harm. Ultimately, whether this evolution represents true progress or a new form of control depends largely on whether the community values personal accountability or shared dignity more.",
